Shelldone is just a shell written in C from scratch so I can play with it.
I guess it will never be as complete as zsh/csh/bash/whatever, but actually it
is not my goal.
I'm just working on it to learn and improve my skills in C programming.

Compilation
-----------

$ make

Execution
---------

$ ./shelldone

Example
-------

It is now possible to run commands using the following operators: ';', '|', '&',
'&&', and '||'.
It still doesn't need any external libraries.
Here is a little demo:

ziirish@carbon:~/workspace/shelldone$ make
gcc -std=c99 -Wall -Werror -W -fno-builtin -g   -c -o shelldone.o shelldone.c
gcc -std=c99 -Wall -Werror -W -fno-builtin -g   -c -o xutils.o xutils.c
gcc -std=c99 -Wall -Werror -W -fno-builtin -g   -c -o command.o command.c
gcc -std=c99 -Wall -Werror -W -fno-builtin -g   -c -o builtin.o builtin.c
gcc -std=c99 -Wall -Werror -W -fno-builtin -g   -c -o parser.o parser.c
gcc  shelldone.o xutils.o command.o builtin.o parser.o -o shelldone
ziirish@carbon:~/workspace/shelldone$ valgrind ./shelldone
==18100== Memcheck, a memory error detector
==18100== Copyright (C) 2002-2010, and GNU GPL'd, by Julian Seward et al.
==18100== Using Valgrind-3.6.0.SVN-Debian and LibVEX; rerun with -h for
copyright info
==18100== Command: ./shelldone
